14/04/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The trial against 28 people accused of human and car trafficking started on Thursday (13 April) in Skopje. The defendants are policemen, customs officials, taxi drivers and truck drivers from Macedonia, Albania, Bulgaria and Serbia-Montenegro. Prosecutors say they were part of a criminal network that moved illegal immigrants from Macedonia to Greece. (Utrinski Vesnik, A1 TV - 13/04/06)
